# Single Source of Truth

Never duplicate data-fetching or derivation logic across components or pages. If two places need the same data, extract a shared utility.

## Account / Rate Data

**APR resolution** has one function: `resolveApr(lib, accountRates)` in `src/app/account/liabilities/page.tsx`.
- Priority: (1) `lib.interestRate` from statement, (2) `accountRates` matched by **exact** `accountKey === lib.accountSlug`, (3) `APR_CATEGORY_DEFAULTS`
- Never do fuzzy bank-name matching. Both `accountKey` and `accountSlug` are produced by `buildAccountSlug(bankName, accountId)` ‚Äî they are identical.
- `PayoffTab` and `OverviewTab` both call `resolveApr()`. Do not add a third copy.

**Account balance** comes from the `/api/user/statements` response (`UserStatementSummary.netWorth`). Do not re-derive it on individual pages from raw transaction sums.

**Stored rates** come from `/api/user/account-rates`. Match by `accountKey` only. The account detail page, the liabilities overview, and the payoff planner all use this same API ‚Äî they must all match the same way.

## Shared Computations

If the same calculation exists in more than one component, extract it:

```typescript
// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî one module-level function used by all tabs
function resolveApr(lib, accountRates) { ... }

// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äî PayoffTab and OverviewTab each have their own copy
const apr = accountRates.find(r =>
  normalizeName(r.bankName).includes(normalizeName(d.label)) // fuzzy, wrong
);
```

## API Response Fields

When a field is needed on the client, add it to the API response **once** and add it to the TypeScript interface. Do not re-fetch or re-derive it in each component.

- `interestRate` ‚Üí `UserStatementSummary` + `statements/route.ts`
- `source`, `csvDateRange`, `txCount` ‚Üí already in `UserStatementSummary`

## Transaction Logic ‚Äî Transfers & Payments vs Payments Made

These are **two sides of the same transaction** and must never be confused:

| Field | Where recorded | What it means |
|-------|---------------|---------------|
| `Debt Payments` category | Expense on the **asset** account (checking/savings) | CC/loan payment sent FROM checking ‚Äî e.g. "VISA PAYMENT" |
| `Transfers` category | Expense on the **asset** account | Inter-account or e-transfer to a person/business ‚Äî NOT a debt payment |
| `paymentsMade` | Separate field on the **debt** account (CC/loan) | Money received by the debt account ‚Äî tracked for reconciliation |
| `Transfers & Payments` | Legacy only ‚Äî old statements before the split | Treat as equivalent to `Transfers` in display |

**Design rule**: `Debt Payments` on the asset side offsets `paymentsMade` on the debt side. True discretionary spending = `This Month total ‚àí paymentsMade`. Always show both AND the net when `paymentsMade > 0`.

**Category taxonomy** (canonical, used in both `csvParser.ts` and `parseStatement.ts`):
`Dining`, `Groceries`, `Shopping`, `Transportation`, `Entertainment`, `Subscriptions`, `Healthcare`, `Fees`, `Debt Payments`, `Investments & Savings`, `Transfers`, `Cash & ATM`, `Other`, `Income`

- `Fees` ‚Äî bank/account/NSF/overdraft fees (O.D.P. FEE, MONTHLY ACCOUNT FEE), service charges, annual card fees

- `Debt Payments` ‚Äî CC/loan/mortgage payments FROM a checking account (matches `paymentsMade` on debt side)
- `Investments & Savings` ‚Äî RRSP/TFSA/mutual fund contributions, life insurance premiums, investment-linked insurance
- `Transfers` ‚Äî inter-account or e-transfers to people/businesses (not debt or investment)
- `Transfers & Payments` ‚Äî legacy label only; treat as `Transfers` in display

**Sign rules** (defined once in `csv-import/route.ts` and `csvParser.ts` ‚Äî never re-implement elsewhere):
- Asset account (checking/savings): outgoing = expense, incoming = income
- Debt account (CC/loan/mortgage): outgoing = expense, incoming = `paymentsMade` (NOT income)
